cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on setting up a reinforcement learning task with a real-world robot. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the challenges of learning with real-world robots and proposes mitigating steps. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as reinforcement learning is a subfield of AI. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper discusses the sensitivity of learning performance to the setup, which is related to control systems. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on visual perception, but the UR5 robotic arm used in the study has a camera attached to it, which may involve some computer vision techniques.
